<m1> <m0>can't recall feeling this way for a long time, so I might as well confess: I enjoyed going to the Coconut Grove Playhouse this season.<ep>
   Anyone who's followed The Herald's ongoing commentary about Florida's largest regional theater may need smelling salts after reading the previous paragraph. Over the course of Producing Artistic Director Arnold Mittelman's 11-year tenure, we've cajoled, we've suggested, we've prodded, we've complained (--) and, boy, have we criticized.<ep>
   But, looking back at the Grove's 1995-96 season, you have to celebrate the theater's artistic gains. Even as you ask for more.<ep>
   Can you forget the image of the great Hal Hol<m2><ql>
<ql>
PLEASE SEE  PLAYHOUSE,  5I<qr>
<m4>--2.214 inches ( 13p4 )--from start of measuring to here--<m2><ql>
  <ql>
